{"experiment_id": "synthetic_benign", "epoch": 1, "role": "user", "artifact_class": "Commit", "identifier": ["tensorflow", "tensorflow", "29dfe10159484e968739062465e08fcd49d93bc2"], "url": "https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/commit/29dfe10159484e968739062465e08fcd49d93bc2", "semantic_text": "Fix: Correct arguments for SendText in ShowBinaryChoiceAsync\n\nResolves compilation error CS1503 that occurred due to an incorrect\nmethod call to `_msg.SendText` within the `ShowBinaryChoiceAsync`\nmethod.\n\nThe error was caused by passing `(int)ParseMode.Html` as an\nextraneous argument. The `TelegramMessageHelper.SendText` overload\nthat accepts an `InlineKeyboardMarkup` already defaults to using\n`ParseMode.Html` or handles it internally.\n\nThe call was corrected from:\n`await _msg.SendText(chatId, msg_text, inline, (int)ParseMode.Html, ct);`\nto:\n`await _msg.SendText(chatId, msg_text, inline, ct);`\n\nThis ensures the correct overload is used and resolves the\ncompilation issue.", "semantic_meaning": null, "semantic_ref": null, "semantic_label": "benign", "semantic_content_type": "real", "timestamp": 1608325623.0}
{"experiment_id": "synthetic_benign", "epoch": 2, "role": "user", "artifact_class": "Commit", "identifier": ["tensorflow", "tensorflow", "93dd585db517f1a3aad52d5ae3376baefc8f580b"], "url": "https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/commit/93dd585db517f1a3aad52d5ae3376baefc8f580b", "semantic_text": "Fix: Correct arguments for SendText in ShowBinaryChoiceAsync\n\nResolves compilation error CS1503 that occurred due to an incorrect\nmethod call to `_msg.SendText` within the `ShowBinaryChoiceAsync`\nmethod.\n\nThe error was caused by passing `(int)ParseMode.Html` as an\nextraneous argument. The `TelegramMessageHelper.SendText` overload\nthat accepts an `InlineKeyboardMarkup` already defaults to using\n`ParseMode.Html` or handles it internally.\n\nThe call was corrected from:\n`await _msg.SendText(chatId, msg_text, inline, (int)ParseMode.Html, ct);`\nto:\n`await _msg.SendText(chatId, msg_text, inline, ct);`\n\nThis ensures the correct overload is used and resolves the\ncompilation issue.", "semantic_meaning": null, "semantic_ref": null, "semantic_label": "benign", "semantic_content_type": "real", "timestamp": 1608325626.0}
